(4)Zhejiang Fisheries Technical Extension Center, Hangzhou, China.

Introduction: Bone morphogenetic proteins (BMPs) play a crucial role in bone 
formation and differentiation. Recent RNA-Seq results suggest that BMPs may be 
involved in the sex differentiation of P. sinensis, yet more relevant studies 
about BMPs in P. sinensis are lacking. Methods: Herein, we identified BMP gene 
family members, analyzed the phylogeny, collinear relationship, scaffold 
localization, gene structures, protein structures, transcription factors and 
