Poor sleep quality is recognized as a major risk factor for poor health, 
increasing the incidence of serious chronic diseases. In people with Down 
syndrome, sleep apnea prevalence is significantly greater, it is caused by 
genetic, anatomical, endocrine, and metabolic abnormalities. The consequences of 
sleep disruption due to sleep apnea are very serious, especially in terms of 
